<question contentItemName="toeflPrac10221">
<categoryRefs>
<catRef-GRAD-UQTopic categoryName="struc.subordclause"/></categoryRefs>
<question-stem>
<para>          What does the professor mean when he says:<mediaExhibit frameType="mp3"
mediaRef="toeflPrac10221_02.mp3"/></para>
</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> Marine biologists do not believe there are isolated
populations of monk seals</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> Marine biologists hope science will find a way to restore
the monk seal population.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> Marine biologists feel the time has come for frank discussion
about pollution in the Caribbean.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> Marine biologists think isolated islands in the Caribbean
offer the best chance of finding populations of monk seals.</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para> The function of the idiomatic expression <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> wishful
thinking </emphasis>is to show that what is desired is impossible, or at least
improbable, to achieve; therefore, marine biologists do not believe that they
exist. <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> Hopes, </emphasis>unlike wishes,
indicate possibilities (B). <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> Frank discussions </emphasis>(C)
and <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> offer the best chance </emphasis>(D)
have nothing to do with the original statement.</para>
</explanation>
</question>
</gradItems>
